\fBNotes:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBclj\fP refers to the bare \fBclojure\fR CLI REPL without third-party
tools.
With rebel-readline, clj gains completion, multiline editing, and
syntax highlighting.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBbb\fP refers to Babashka v1.12+ which uses JLine3 for its console
REPL.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBlein repl\fP uses REPL-y (JLine-based) for its console interface.

.SH Web REPL
The Gloat website includes a browser-based REPL powered by Glojure
compiled to WebAssembly.
It provides a subset of the CLI REPL's features and requires no
installation.

.SS How It Works
The web REPL loads a Glojure Wasm binary (\fBglj.wasm\fR) and runs it
inside the browser.
User input is fed to the Wasm runtime through a hooked \fBstdin\fR, and
evaluation output is captured from \fBstdout\fR/\fBstderr\fR and displayed
in the terminal pane.

.PP
The REPL initializes automatically when the page loads.
A loading spinner is shown while the Wasm binary downloads and
initializes.

.SS Supported Features
The web REPL supports the following features:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSyntax highlighting\fP -- the same token types as the CLI REPL
(strings, keywords, comments, numbers, booleans, special forms,
core functions) are highlighted as you type.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBRainbow brackets\fP -- brackets are colored by nesting depth
using the same Calva-style color scheme as the CLI REPL.
Mismatched and unmatched brackets are shown with white text on a
red background.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBMultiline input\fP -- incomplete expressions (unclosed brackets
or strings) automatically continue on the next line with
indentation matching the nesting depth.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBHistory\fP -- Up/Down arrows (or Ctrl+P/Ctrl+N) navigate through
previous inputs within the session.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSmart indentation\fP -- Tab inserts two spaces.
Backspace deletes two spaces at once when preceded by two spaces,
matching the CLI's indent-aware behavior.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBEditing shortcuts\fP -- Ctrl+A (beginning of line), Ctrl+E (end
of line), Ctrl+U (kill before cursor), Ctrl+K (kill after cursor),
Ctrl+L (clear screen).
.IP \(bu 2
\fBPaste support\fP -- pasted text is inserted as plain text with
carriage returns normalized and trailing newlines stripped.

.SS Toolbar
The toolbar above the terminal provides quick-access buttons:

.TS
allbox;
l l 
l l .
\fBButton\fP	\fBAction\fP
Share	T{
Copy a shareable URL (with input state) to clipboard
T}
Copy	T{
Copy the current form (or last history entry) to clipboard
T}
Up/Down	Navigate history
Kill left/right	Delete before/after cursor
Clear	Clear the terminal output
.TE

.SS Sharing
The web REPL supports sharing expressions via URL fragments.
When you type or evaluate expressions, the URL hash is updated with
a base64-encoded snapshot of your history.
Sharing this URL loads the REPL with the same expressions
pre-evaluated, and the last expression placed in the input field
ready to run.

.SS Limitations
The web REPL does not support:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBTab completion\fP -- there is no completion menu; Tab inserts
spaces.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBGhost text\fP (autosuggestions).
.IP \(bu 2
\fBVi/Emacs editing modes\fP -- only basic editing is available.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBPersistent history\fP -- history is lost when the page is
reloaded.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBCtrl+D documentation lookup\fP\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBnREPL server\fP -- the Wasm runtime runs entirely in the browser.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBExternal Go dependencies\fP -- only the built-in standard library
and clojure.core are available.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSuspend/resume\fP (Ctrl+Z).

.SS CLI vs Web REPL Feature Matrix
.TS
